      {
        "id": 2967552,
        "name": "Doug Lee",
        "username": "Doug_Lee",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/doug_lee/{size}/787_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-29T15:54:24.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=2404\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>1996 Ch\u00e2teau Montrose</strong></a> <em>- France, Bordeaux, M\u00e9doc, St. Est\u00e8phe (8/28/2020)</em><br>\nDecanted for 45 minutes and followed for 3 hours.  Opaque garnet with scarlet edges. Nose of savory green elements mixed with fecund soil, lifted floral notes, cassis, pencil lead, and currant. Seemingly settled layers of black currant, fine green leaf, and black plum on the palate nonetheless deepening with grip and lithe, earthen gravity. Lively acidity and softened tannin leading to a long finish of currant, soil, wild green, a bit of sauvage, and tobacco. Vital complexity within a civilized frame. <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
